claim.claim-text:
A currency acceptor assembly comprising:
a currency passageway;
a mounting assembly arranged along a length of the currency passageway;
a currency storage assembly having an entrance coupled to the currency passageway, the currency passageway being arranged to guide a currency denomination in a forward direction to the entrance of the currency storage assembly; and
an actuated castellation plate mounted to the mounting assembly and
configured to transfer between an open state and a closed state.

A currency acceptor comprising:
a means for transporting a currency denomination along a currency passageway in a forward direction to an entrance of a currency storage assembly;
a means for transferring a castellation plate between an open state and a closed state along the currency passageway, the open state enabling transporting of the currency denomination in the forward direction and the closed state preventing transporting of the currency denomination in a reverse direction.
